# Claude Code / Archon
# Skills under .claude/skills/ are local developer tooling by default, e.g. the
# Archon CLI installs `archon` and `manage-run` here via `archon skill install`.
# Ignore everything under skills/ and explicitly re-include only the
# project-owned skills we want versioned. Add a matching `!` line when
# introducing a new one.
.claude/skills/*
!.claude/skills/3common-sdk-conventions/
# Local-only Claude Code settings (a shared .claude/settings.json, if added, is
# fine).
.claude/settings.local.json
# .archon/ (config.yaml, workflows/, commands/, the shared workflow definition)
# is committed. Per-run artifacts/logs normally live under
# ~/.archon/workspaces/<owner>/<repo>/, but for an unregistered repo Archon
# falls back to writing them under <repo>/.archon/, so we ignore those runtime
# dirs so a 4MB spec snapshot + markers never get swept into a generated PR.
.archon/artifacts/
.archon/logs/
# Codex/agents-side mirror: `archon skill install` also drops the bundled
# `archon`/`manage-run` skills under .agents/skills/. No project-owned agent
# skills today, so ignore the whole tree (switch to the .claude/skills/*
# whitelist pattern above if you ever add a project skill here).
.agents/
